The paper deals with the evaluation of determinants, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of computer algebra methods, specifically the holonomic ansatz, is a major focus of the paper, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.SC (symbolic computation) and cs.CC (computational complexity). The paper also mentions the counting of plane partitions and rhombus tilings, which are topics in combinatorics (cs.GT). Finally, the paper uses computer algorithms to prove conjectures, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.NA (numerical analysis).
